vivae.util
Class SVGShapeLoader

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Thread
      vivae.util.SVGShapeLoader
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
public class SVGShapeLoader
extends java.lang.Thread

SVShapeLoader loads an SVG file, creates a DOM from it, searches for all known types of ArenaPart and can return a map of shapes indexed by their type. It also works with layers in the SVG file, so you can get a Vector with such a map for each layer. To use it, create it's instance, run it as a thread and then get the Shapes by calling getShapesWithTypeMap.

getShapesWithTypeMap

public java.util.Vector<java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.Vector<java.awt.Shape>>> getShapesWithTypeMap()
After the maps of the shapes has been created when this instance had ran as a thread and the method isAllDone() returns true, the shapes are prepared in the structure you get from this method.

Returns:
A vector that contains a map for each layer in the SVG input file. Each Map is indexed by a ArenaPart type, for example "obstacle" and contains a vector of shapes the Obstacles will be constructed from.
